Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. CONDITIONS MODIFIED 05/20/2022:  The Court will allow contact with the defendants estranged wife.  The defendant is to have no violent contact with his estranged wife and further shall not discuss this case with her. 

PREVIOUS CONDITIONS: Defendant to have no contact with Victim A/Victim B/Witness A/his sisters and their significant others listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney.  Defendant to comply with GPS monitoring through Wisconsin Community Services.  Defendant to be released during regular business hours only and is to report directly to Wisconsin Community Services upon release.  Defendant not to leave the State of Wisconsin without prior authorization from the Court.  Defendant is not to possess any firearms.  Defendant is to turnover any firearms in his possession to the Waukesha County Sheriff's Department within 24 hours upon being released from custody.  Defendant is to comply with any treatment ordered in any parallel case.  Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.

09:11 AM Defendant Jared A Hassin in court with attorney Jonathan Carver Smith.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court addresses:  Defense Motion to Modify Bond.  Attorney Smith requests GPS be removed and further modification of the no contact order.  Attorney Smith presents arguments in support of the motion to modify.  State presents arguments and objects to the removal of GPS and would request if the Court modified the no contact order that it be modified to a no violent contact order with his estranged wife.  Court will allow contact with the estranged wife but it is to be no violent contact and further the defendant shall not discuss this case with her.  The request for removal of GPS is denied.  Defendant to report to room C226 to sign the amended bond.
